results.title: Where Walks the True Believer!
results.description: Star Brand meets Nightmask.

results.title: A Summers Tale
results.description: Alex's early life is explored in flashback. He is adopted by the Blandings to replace their older son, Todd.  Todd was an excellent athlete and scholar, and despite trying his best, Alex doesn't ever quite measure up.  Some local bullies and Mr. Sinister want to make sure Alex never fits it, however.

results.title: Third Genesis
results.description: The original X-Men find out that Jean Grey is still alive and gather for a reunion; Jean explains her near-death experience and the Phoenix phenomenon; The team decides to form X-Factor, a group of mutant hunters whose real purpose is to rescue and help new mutants; Navy man Rusty Collins manifests destructive flame powers and X-Factor brings him in.

items.name: Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 7 (2007)
Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 7 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Fallen Angel!
results.description: After a pitched battle with the Marauders in the Morlock tunnels, Angel's wings are pierced by Harpoon.

results.title: Mahapralaya
results.description: X-Factor tries to prevent Haven from ending the world in the quest for future enlightenment; Once Haven's plans have been defeated, she tries to cure Multiple Man of the legacy virus but he dies.

results.title: Afterlives
results.description: X-Factor mourns Jamie's death; Havok quits.

results.title: Friends and Family
results.description: Guido takes Rahne and Random home to meet the family; Malice possesses Havok.

results.title: Malicious Intent!
results.description: Havok as Malice takes down Polaris.

results.title: Final Sacrifice
results.description: Malice is destroyed.

results.title: Strong Guy in "Punch-O-Rama"
results.description: Guido vs. Blob.

results.title: Promised Vengeance
results.description: Mystique attempts to kill Legion for his part in Destiny's death; Legion wakes up from his coma.

results.title: The Waking
results.description: Mystique vs. Legion

results.title: Redemption!
results.description: X-Factor tries to save a group of untrusting Morlocks from the Marauders, but the group leaves their rescuers and runs up against the police instead; Boom Boom quits stealing for the Vanisher; Doctors tell Cyclops and Jean that Angel's wings will have to be amputated.

results.title: Creatures On the Loose
results.description: X-Factor fights aliens in Madripoor.

results.title: Explosive Performances
results.description: X-Factor fights aliens in Madripoor; Guido has a Heart Attack (Next Appearance in X-Factor #133).

results.title: Impulsive Behavior
results.description: X-Factor is in Japan trying to rescue Havok from Fatale and helping him keep his powers under control.

results.title: That Certain Mystique
results.description: X-Factor tries to get its act together and cope with changes in the roster.

results.title: A Walk on the Wild Side!
Home Comings
results.description: A half-crazed Aurora comes gunning for Wildchild for spurning what she thought was their love for each other.

results.title: Adversaries
results.description: Haven gives birth to the Adversary; Dark Beast lures Havok away from the team.

results.title: Havok's Fall
results.description: Havok is beaten by Random and captured by Dark Beast; The Adversary defeats Naze and goes after Forge.

results.title: The Best Offense
results.description: Forge and X-Factor take on The Adversary.

results.title: Boom Boom Boom!
results.description: Boom Boom calls X-Factor to help her escape the clutches of the Vanisher; Jean tries to find her sister; Scott decides to return to Alaska and his wife.

results.title: Meeting the Maker
results.description: The government forces X-Factor to take Sabretooth as a member.

results.title: The True Path
results.description: Forge has a final showdown with the Adversary.

results.title: A Fact You Can Count On...
The Face of Things to Come...
Future Memories
results.description: X-Factor tries to see how Sabretooth will work with the team; Shard reappears and joins her old friends; Random is sent by Fatale to infiltrate X-Factor again.

results.title: Onslaught Impact 1: Re-Creating Havok in McCoy's Image
The Ticking Clock
results.description: X-Factor battles Onslaught's minions who are being led by a mind-controlled Havok; They fight valiantly, but cannot stop the bad guys from putting Onslaught's plans into motion; Havok is captured by Polaris; Random is revealed as a plant for the Dark Beast's Brotherhood.

items.name: X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 2 (2008)
X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 2 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Free Fall
results.description: X-Factor pierces the Dark Beast's disguise and finds out what he did with the real McCoy.

items.name: X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 2 (2008)
X-Men: The Complete Onslaught Epic Book 2 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Onslaught Impact 2: The Beast or Not the Beast--That Is the Question
The Beast Within
results.description: X-Factor avoids the Dark Beast's deceptions and rescues the real Beast; Havok and Random face off over Polaris, but the winner then takes Polaris down.

results.title: Darker Destiny
results.description: The Friends of Humanity beat up a boy under Mystique's care, and Mystique vows to kill Graydon Creed as he is the group's leader.

results.title: Night of the Hounds
results.description: X-Factor is sent out to hunt a band of rogue mutants, only to find that they are all Jamie Madrox, The Multiple Man.

results.title: Ghosts!
results.description: Master Mold awakens and heads for Cyclops; Scott leaves for Alaska to find his wife and child but discovers that all records of them have been erased like they never really existed.

results.title: A Mother's Eyes
results.description: The assassination of Graydon Creed takes place by a mysterious shooter.

results.title: Brotherhood
results.description: Havok rescues the Dark Beast from his government captors and begins his own version of the Brotherhood with himself as leader.

results.title: Breakaway
results.description: Forge and X-Factor tender their resignations as government agents; Shard gets closer to befriending Jamie with Wildchild in tow; A boy that Mystique has an interest in is kidnapped and she goes to the family for help and support; The Falls Edge base totally self destructs with X-Factor inside; Forge and Mystique die in a fiery car crash.

results.title: Down Under
results.description: Forge fakes X-Factor's death to get out from under government control; Havok tries to recruit Madrox for the Brotherhood; Guido twitches.

results.title: The Child
results.description: Guido is out of his coma (From injuries in X-Factor #111); X-Factor finds Trevor.

results.title: Because You Demanded It...The Return of Strong Guy
A Virtual Reality
results.description: X-Factor and Multiple Man attempt to save Guido from the government without provoking another heart attack in the big galoot.

results.title: Jeoparody
results.description: Guido plays the game show Jeoparody in which all of the questions and answers have something to do with the Strong Guy Reborn one-shot soon to be published.

results.title: Nothing Lasts Forever
results.description: Sabretooth is freed from Forge's control by his allies in Zero Tolerance and goes on a tear through the mansion carving up X-Factor.

results.title: It Was a Dark & Stormy Night
results.description: Sabretooth heads out after Trevor; In the hospital with injuries from their fight with Sabretooth, X-Factor is protected by Val and her ex-husband Edmond as government forces close in; Havok shows up for an assist.

results.title: Fear Walks Amongst Us
results.description: Havok's Brotherhood helps X-Factor recoup from their injuries; Sabretooth goes toe-to-toe with Omega Red.
